    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "The `getCommentLikes` method uses `frame.data.id` to extract the comment ID, but the endpoint definition in comment-likes.js specifies `id` in the `options` array (query parameters), not in the request body. This causes the commentId to be undefined. Other similar methods like `getCommentReporters` correctly use `frame.options.id`. This inconsistency will cause the request to fail.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/ghost/core/core/server/services/comments/comments-controller.js
